===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|u-turn}}

===Etymology===
[[U]] + [[turn]], from the similarity to the shape of the letter ''U''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-PerfectSoundWhatever-U-turn.wav|Audio (CA)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[U]]-[[turn]]}}

# {{lb|en|literally}} A [[turn]] in a [[vehicle]] carried out by driving in a [[semicircle]] in order to travel in the [[opposite]] [[direction]].
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} A reversal of [[policy]]; an [[about-face]], a [[backflip]].
#: {{ux|en|The government have done a '''U-turn''' and are now supporting greater European integration instead of opposing it.}}

====Usage notes====
* Often used in the phrases {{m|en||do a U-turn}} or {{m|en||make a U-turn}}.

====Synonyms====
* {{l|en|uey}} {{q|colloquial}}

